## Setup & Configuration

### Basic pytest Configuration

Add to your `pyproject.toml`:

```toml
[tool.pytest.ini_options]
testpaths = ["tests"]
python_files = "test_*.py"
python_classes = "Test*"
python_functions = "test_*"
markers = [
    "unit: Unit tests",
    "integration: Integration tests",
    "functional: Functional tests",
    "slow: Tests that take longer than 1s to run",
    "network: Tests that require network access",
]
filterwarnings = [
    "ignore::DeprecationWarning:distutils",
    "ignore::DeprecationWarning:pkg_resources",
]
asyncio_mode = "auto"
```

### Configuring Coverage

Add to your `pyproject.toml`:

```toml
[tool.coverage.run]
source = ["crawl4ai_mcp"]
omit = [
    "*/test_*.py",
    "*/__init__.py",
    "*/conftest.py",
]

[tool.coverage.report]
exclude_lines = [
    "pragma: no cover",
    "def __repr__",
    "if self.debug",
    "raise NotImplemented" + "Error",
    "if __name__ == .__main__.:",
    "if TYPE_CHECKING:",
    "pass",
]
```

### Test Organization

Organize tests to mirror your application structure:

```
crawl4ai_mcp/               # Application code
└── module/
    └── file.py
tests/                      # Test code
└── module/
    └── test_file.py        # Tests for file.py
```

### Fixture Best Practices

Create a central `conftest.py` with shared fixtures:

```python
"""Shared test fixtures for the crawl4ai_mcp tests."""

import pytest
from pathlib import Path
from typing import Generator

@pytest.fixture
def sample_data_dir() -> Path:
    """Return the path to the sample data directory."""
    return Path(__file__).parent / "data"

@pytest.fixture
def mock_http_client(mocker: pytest.MockFixture) -> mocker.Mock:
    """Create a mock HTTP client for testing."""
    mock = mocker.patch("crawl4ai_mcp.http.client")
    mock.get.return_value.status_code = 200
    mock.get.return_value.text = "<html><body>Test</body></html>"
    return mock

@pytest.fixture
async def cleanup_temp_files() -> Generator[None, None, None]:
    """Clean up temporary files after tests."""
    temp_files = []
    
    # Fixture yields control to the test
    yield
    
    # Cleanup after test completes
    for file in temp_files:
        file.unlink(missing_ok=True)
```

## Verification

To run all tests and generate coverage report:

```bash
make test-cov
```

For focused testing during development:

```bash
pytest -xvs tests/path/to/test_file.py::TestClass::test_function
```

For property-based testing with detailed output:

```bash
pytest --hypothesis-show-statistics -xvs tests/path/to/test_property.py
```